<paragraph blockId="38.[264,1323,284,1809]" box="[312,569,1335,1361]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Distribution. ‘Africa’.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[264,1323,284,1809]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Remarks. In addition to the characters in the key, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Hull" authorityYear="1962" box="[899,1042,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaculator">
<emphasis box="[899,1042,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">O. jaculator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is further distinguished by the dense white setae and two long pencil­like bristles on the face, the narrow cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1303,1315,1426,1447]" fontSize="9" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">4</subScript>
, the unusually short apical petiole of cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[752,760,1473,1488]" fontSize="6" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">1</subScript>
and wide cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[955,965,1472,1489]" fontSize="7" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">1</subScript>
, and a weak ventral concavity on the basal half of the middle femur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[264,1323,284,1809]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Hull" authorityYear="1962" box="[312,548,1543,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaculator">
<emphasis box="[312,548,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Ommatius jaculator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the male 
<typeStatus box="[915,1017,1543,1569]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">holotype</typeStatus>
that is in poor condition. The fore legs except coxae, all tarsi except the basal tarsomere of the right hind tarsus, and abdomen are absent. Label data include: 1) round label with green margin and the word ‘type’; 2) white rectangular label with ‘0rce’or ‘Oru’?; 3) white rectangular label with ‘68 4’; 4) white rectangular label with ‘Africa, pres. W. W. Saunders, B.M. 1868­4’; and 5) red margined label with the word ‘Holotype’, 6) rectangular label with ‘ 
<typeStatus box="[1063,1178,1743,1769]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaculator">Ommatius jaculator Walker</taxonomicName>
, det. J. E. Chainey, 1986.’
</paragraph>
